    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-10-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-10-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="336"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d336">
                <head>336. Letter From Foreign Secretary <persName corresp="#p_LSJSB1" type="from"
                        >Lloyd</persName> to Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_DJF1"
                        type="to">Dulles</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d336fn1">Source: Department of State,
                        Conference Files: Lot 62 D 181, CF 928. Top Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                                when="1957-10-25">October 25, 1957</date>.</hi>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Foster</persName>
                    </hi>: I write to confirm what I said to you last night about China’s
                    representation in the United Nations.<note n="2" xml:id="d336fn2">See <ref
                            target="#d322">Document 322</ref>.</note> The present Government of the
                    United Kingdom will not seek or support, without prior agreement with the United
                    States Government, any change in regard to the representation of China in the
                    United Nations, its dependent agencies and other international organisations in
                    which this question may arise.</p>
                <p>Yours ever</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Selwyn</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
